addController(address).details: Authorises a controller, who can register and renew domains.

addReservedTokenId(uint256[]).details: Some names are reserved for special purposes

available(uint256).details: Returns true iff the specified name is available for registration.

nameExpires(uint256).details: Returns the expiration timestamp of the specified id.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Gets the owner of the specified token ID. Names become unowned      when their registration expires.

params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query the owner of

returns._0: address currently marked as the owner of the given token ID

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

reclaim(uint256,address).details: Reclaim ownership of a name in MID, if you own it in the registrar.

params.duration: Duration in seconds for the registration.
params.id: The token ID (keccak256 of the label).
params.owner: The address that should own the registration.

registerOnly(uint256,address,uint256).details: Register a name, without modifying the registry.

params.duration: Duration in seconds for the registration.
params.id: The token ID (keccak256 of the label).
params.owner: The address that should own the registration.

removeController(address).details: Revoke controller permission for an address.

renew(uint256,uint256).details: Renew the name with input duration

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: modify `transferFrom` and `safeTransferFrom` to make the domain automatically  transfer to target owner as well

setResolver(address).details: Set the resolver for the TLD this registrar manages.

tokenByIndex(uint256).details: Get token ID by stored order

tokenURI(uint256).details: Return the metadata URI by token ID

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: modify `transferFrom` and `safeTransferFrom` to make the domain automatically  transfer to target owner as well

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

idToIndexes.details: mapping from token id to index in tokens array

maxMintPerUser.details: The max minting count per account

ownerToIds.details: mapping from owner address to token ids
